   Up Arrow to Map   1. Tokeland Boat Launch

        Waterbody: Willapa Bay
        Site Manager: Willapa Harbor Port of
        Nearest City: Tokeland


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp
                            1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     10 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            60 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        SR 105 to Tokeland on Tokeland Rd (becomes Kindred Ave); L on Front
        Lane, go .1 mi to launch area.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate grade and adequate traction. Abrupt
        edges are developing on the sides of the ramp. A fee is charged to
        use the boat ramp. Moorage is also available for a fee. A
        convenience store is located next to the boat ramp. R.V. campsites
        and a restroom facility are also located near the boat ramp area.


   Up Arrow to Map   2. North River Resort

        Waterbody: North River
        Site Manager: North River Resort
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Flush
     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     5 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            5 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Raymond, W on SR 105 10.5 mi; R at resort.
        Site Description:

        A fee is charged for using the ramp and parking a vehicle. North
        River Resort also has R.V. hook-ups, a play area, cabins, and boat
        moorage. The resort is closed during the off season.


   Up Arrow to Map   3. Smith Creek (WDFW)

        Waterbody: Smith Creek
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     20 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            60 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - site will flood during extreme high tide (10 feet +). Access
        to Willapa Bay may be difficult at high tide because of the height
        of the US101 bridge crossing Smith Creek.

        Driving Directions:

        From Raymond, W on SR 105 10.2 mi; cross Smith Creek, turn R to ramp
        area.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate grade. The ramp area has been widened
        due to heavy use. Area tends to flood during high tide and heavy
        runoff. There are bullet holes in the steel door to the vault
        toilet. The concrete walls of the vault have been shot several times
        creating pock marks in the wall face. WSDOT had set up a scale
        operation in the parking area during the time of the site visit. A
        high tide of ten feet or more will cover the entire parking area.
        The US101 bridge crossing Smith Creek may be too low for some boats
        to go under during high tide.


   Up Arrow to Map   4. Helen Davis Memorial Park

        Waterbody: Willapa River
        Site Manager: South Bend City of
        Nearest City: South Bend


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     6 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            7 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From South Bend, W on US 101 .2 mi; boat ramp is in Helen Davis
        Memorial Park.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate grade. Concrete has been placed along
        the sides of the ramp to prevent erosion. Several of the concrete
        planks are broken or disintegrating at mid-ramp. Steel fasteners are
        completely corroded through at mid-ramp. No overnight parking or
        camping within the parking area. A WDFW sign at the entrance to the
        ramp informs boaters to avoid gill net boats. The park also has
        picnic tables and park benches, but no restroom facilities.


   Up Arrow to Map   5. Raymond Riverfront Park

        Waterbody: Willapa River
        Site Manager:
        Nearest City: Raymond


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Flush
     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            2 Concrete Ramp
                            2 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     25 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            50 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        Along the S Fork of the Willapa River, go W of SR 101 in downtown
        Raymond; Traveling N on Hwy 101, turn L on Commercial; turn L again
        on 3rd St, travel to parking lot
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate to steep grade with excellent traction.
        The boat ramp area is located within a basin, away from the river
        current. The boat ramp receives some debris washed in from the
        river. Willapa Landing Park also has ballfields, picnic tables, open
        lawn space, and a trail with interpretive signs. Large viewing
        platforms are located next to the ramp area and up the river about
        100 yards.


   Up Arrow to Map   6. Willapa Wilson (WDFW)

        Waterbody: Willapa River
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            2 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     10 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            40 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - ramp and parking aea becomes flooded during tides of 10 feet
        or more.

        Driving Directions:

        From Raymond at SR 6/US 101 junction, N .8 mi on US 101; R (east) on
        Monohan Landing Rd, go 3.5 mi; at Wilson Creek, turn R to ramp.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate grade and is located on a section of
        river with a slow current. The boat ramp and parking area are
        covered with water during high tides of ten feet or more.


   Up Arrow to Map   7. Palix River (WDFW)

        Waterbody: Palix River
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            2 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     5 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            15 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - the boat ramp and parking area can become covered in water
        during exceptional high tides.

        Driving Directions:

        From South Bend, S 15 mi on US 101; cross Palix River, turn L to
        parking area in 500 ft.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp is slightly uneven and developing an abrupt edge on
        the right side of the ramp. The parking area and boat ramp can
        become completely covered with water during high tides. No
        designated disabled parking. Bush Pioneer County Park, which offers
        camping and picnicking, is approximately 2.2 miles west of the boat
        launch site.


   Up Arrow to Map   8. Port of Peninsula/Nahcotta Boat Basin

        Waterbody: Willapa Bay
        Site Manager: Peninsula Port of
        Nearest City: Ocean Park


   Site Amenities:

     Fuel Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Fixed Hoist

   Car Parking Facilities:

     15 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            20 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes - limited operation hours in the winter.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        On SR103 through Ocean Park, R on 275th St.; hoist at end of St.
        Site Description:

        The hoist is closed on weekends October through May. Twenty moorage
        slips are available for twentyt feet or smaller boats. A fee is
        charged for the use of the hoist. Drinking water is available at the
        moorage dock.


   Up Arrow to Map   9. Loomis Lake (WDFW)

