   Up Arrow to Map   11. Willapa National Wildlife Refuge

        Waterbody: Willapa Bay
        Site Manager: US Fish & Wildlife Service
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Gravel Ramp
                            1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     5 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            12 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - extreme high tides will prevent access to the boat ramp.

        Driving Directions:

        From Naselle, W on SR 4 5 mi; W on US 101 3.5 mi; site is across US
        101 from ranger station.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a gentle grade. The parking area next to the water
        is prone to flooding. The vault toilet, phone, and additional
        parking are located across the highway from the boat ramp. As of
        January 1997 a fee will charged for using the boat ramp.


   Up Arrow to Map   12. Resort Hotel (WDFW) - Naselle River

        Waterbody: Naselle River
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     3 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            3 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        In Naselle, S 1 mi on SR 401; L (east) on S Valley Rd, go 100 ft.; L
        on Knappton Rd, go .1 mi to end of Rd.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a gentle to moderate grade and is located on a
        section of river with a slow current. A majority of the ramp is
        protected from the current by the bank cut and vegetation upstream.
        The neighbor to the site complained about not having restroom
        facilities and garbage collection at the site. There is an urgent
        need for a restroom at this site. The neighbor also mentioned that
        the site is very popular during the fall months.


   Up Arrow to Map   13. Fort Canby State Park

        Waterbody: Baker Bay
        Site Manager: State Parks
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Flush
     Water Available

                               Boat Launch Type:

                                 2 Concrete Ramp
                                 1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     4 Paved and Striped Spaces

                               Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                 38 Paved and Striped Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Ilwaco, SW on SR 100 Loop 2.5 mi; S on SR 100 Spur .25 mi;
        enter Fort Canby State Park, turn L; go .1 mi to ramp.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate grade. Debris will collect on the ramp
        sometimes making it difficult to launch and load. A fee is charged
        for the use of the ramp. A cleaning station is also available for a
        fee. Additional parking for the boat ramp area is available near the
        entrance to the park. The restrooms have no hard surface leading
        from the parking area to the building and are also locked during the
        winter months. Fort Canby State Park also has campsites, day-use
        areas, beach access, trails, an interpretive center, public phones,
        and a small store.


   Up Arrow to Map   14. Ilwaco Boat Launch

        Waterbody: Baker Bay
        Site Manager: Ilwaco Port of
        Nearest City: Ilwaco


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Flush
     Water Available

                                Boat Launch Type:

                                  2 Concrete Ramp
                                  2 Fixed Hoist
                                  3 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     25 Paved and Striped Spaces

                                Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                  45 Paved and Striped Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        In Ilwaco, S on Elizabeth St. to St. end.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp is in excellent condition. Boat moorage slips are
        available adjacent to the launching facilities. A fee is charged for
        the use of the boat ramp ($4.00). A private fuel dock is also
        adjacent to the boat ramps. No designated disabled parking for
        vehicle and trailers. Boaters on the internet can access the Port of
        Ilwaco homepage for additional information about this launch at
        www.portofilwaco.com


   Up Arrow to Map   15. Port of Chinook

        Waterbody: Baker Bay
        Site Manager: Chinook Port of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Flush
     Fuel Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            2 Concrete Ramp
                            1 Fixed Hoist
                            2 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     25 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            65 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        On US 101 in Chinook, W on W Portl; St; go 1 block, straight at stop
        sign to boat ramp.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate grade with traction hindered from algae
        growth. The ramp surface is uneven due to the previous patching. The
        large breakwater protects the marina and boat ramp. The site also
        has a motor oil collection site, public phone, and moorage slips. No
        overnight camping in the parking area. No designated disabled
        parking. There is a fee to use the boat ramp ($3.00). A sign states
        that the generated revenues go back into the maintenance of the ramp
        area. There is also a fee charged to use the hoists (dependent on
        the footage of the vessel). An appointment is necessary to use the
        hoist after September. The loading floats appear to have been
        recently renovated.


   Up Arrow to Map   16. Chinook County Park (Pacific Co.)

        Waterbody: Baker Bay
        Site Manager: Pacific County Parks & Rec
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Asphalt Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     15 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            30 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - trailerable boats may be only able to launch/ load at high
        tides, but hand launching can occur at any tide.

        Driving Directions:

        From Ilwaco, E on US 101 7.5 mi; R on Chinook Park Rd, go 400 ft.; R
        on gravel Rd to boat ramp.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate to steep grade on the asphalt, the
        grade then flattens out to gentle on the rock and sand. There is an
        abrupt drop off at the end of the asphalt ramp. Debris collects at
        the ramp area. Concrete and large rock protect the ramp from
        erosion. A small picnic area is located 200 feet to the left of the
        boat ramp. Drinking water and restrooms are just inside the gate to
        Chinook County Park. Chinook County Park also has lawn areas, play
        equipment, and beach access. The park area, excluding the ramp, is
        day-use only.


   Up Arrow to Map   17. Knappton Boat Launch

        Waterbody: Columbia River
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            2 Natural Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     1 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            1 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Astoria Bridge, E on SR 401, 4 mi; just after milepost 4, turn
        R to small gravel lot.
        Site Description:

        The approach down to the launch area has a significant drop off and
        is uneven. The ramp grade is gentle with a rock base. Pilings
        surround the ramp area and the access out to the river. Pilings have
        also been cut to provide a launch and loading lane at the site.
        Knappton is the site of an old cannery and is on the State
        Historical Register. No other amenities are at this site. Parking is
        limited, but most likely occurs along SR401.



